---
description: Commit and push Mac changes after major updates; provide Linux pull commands
alwaysApply: true
---

After each major code or docs update on Mac:

1. Commit all relevant changes (exclude secrets: `configs/.env`, `*.pem`, tokens; exclude large artifacts: `docs/OMEIA_app_code_bundle.md`, `tests/*_last_run.json`).
2. Push to `origin` on the current feature branch.
3. End the response with Linux pull/sync commands:

```bash
cd ~/data4TB/digital-notepad
git pull
eval "$(./scripts/dev/load_env.sh configs/.env)"
# Run migrations/reindex only when schema or vectors changed:
# PYTHONPATH=. .venv/bin/python3 scripts/database/apply_sql_migrations.py
# PYTHONPATH=. .venv/bin/python3 scripts/ingest/reindex_vectors.py --limit 5000
./scripts/start_linux.sh   # or restart API if already running
```

Branch: `cursor/unified-search-ai-lab-assistant` unless user specifies otherwise.
